      <scopecontent id="aspace_35712aadee3ea73ba06ae8d29b94e8e9">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection contains numerous designs of unknown origin depicting scenes from the traditional Japanese stage. The scenes displayed are derived from Noh (or Nō) dramas, a performance tradition which draws on Buddhist scripture and Japanese mythology and combines music, dance, and poetry in a highly formalized staging.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
